Durban - Two children were killed after being hit by a minibus taxi in Newlands on Thursday. 

The children, aged 6 and 11, were on their way to school at the time. 

Emergency Medical Services spokesperson, Robert Mckenzie, said when paramedics arrived at the scene they found that both children had sustained fatal injuries. 

“They were declared deceased at the scene. Police were at the scene and will be investigating further. We send our condolences to the families of both children,” Mckenzie said. 

Meanwhile, video footage has emerged from a crash that claimed a life on the N3, near Shongweni earlier this week. In the video, which has been widely shared on social media, a Nissan X Trail is seen veering off the road, over the centre median and into oncoming traffic in the opposite direction. 














